Hello! :wave::skin-tone-3:
I’m adding the HubSpot Conversations widget to our Angular app for <http://Touca.io|Touca.io>. We’d like to `load` and `open` the widget when a user clicks our custom “Send us a message” button and then `remove` that widget when user attempts to close the widget by clicking the HubSpot icon. I’ve implemented the first part (lmk if impl can be improved):
```  openChatWidget() {
    (window as any).HubSpotConversations?.widget.load();
    (window as any).HubSpotConversations?.widget.open();
  }```
I’d like to ask for help to implement the second part. When should `remove` be called? What event should I listen to, to capture clicking the HubSpot icon when the widget is already open?
